<statement>
<p>Instructions call for producing a solution of Sustacal that contains 3 mL of the provided liquid solute with 1 mL of diluent. What is the</p>
<p>dilution ratio: <fillin characters="20" />   </p>
<p>
  dilution factor: <fillin characters="20" />   </p>
<p>
  percent concentration: <fillin characters="20" />   <percent/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{3}</m></li><li><m>\displaystyle\frac{{3}}{{4}}{\quad\text{or}\quad}{1.3333333333333}</m></li><li>75</li></ul></p><p>Dilution ratio is <m>\displaystyle\frac{{\text{solute}}}{{\text{diluent}}}=\frac{{{3}\ \text{ mL}}}{{{1}\ \text{ mL}}}={3}</m></p>
<p>Dilution factor is <m>\displaystyle\frac{{\text{solute}}}{{\text{total}}}=\frac{{{3}\ \text{ mL}}}{{{3}+{1}\ \text{ mL}}}=\frac{{3}}{{4}}{\quad\text{or}\quad}{1.3333333333333}</m></p>
<p>Percent concentration is <m>\displaystyle\frac{{\text{solute}}}{{\text{diluent}}}{100}=\frac{{{3}\ \text{ mL}}}{{{3}+{1}\ \text{ mL}}}{100}={75}\%</m></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

